{
  "stem": "25591.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I mean, we-- you know, we knew the history of the persecution of the Jews through the centuries, but even in Spain in 1492, it was an expulsion and not, not a Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I not only understood the basic facts that Germany took over Austria, but I also understood that many of the Austrians loved it, and, and that the, the German troops were received.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And subsequently, of course, I have seen motion pictures of this with tremendous adulation, and excitement, and joy.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Austrians, with great skill over the years, have attempted to paint Austria as the first victim of Hitler, when in point of fact, to an overwhelming extent, they were the first co-conspirator with Hitler.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I, I don't think I was sophisticated enough to analyze it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But perhaps subliminally, I felt that while Austria had been a separate country, it was nevertheless a German speaking country.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And there was some, some difference between Nazi Germany taking over another German country, German-speaking country, and Hungary, which was very different, linguistically, historically, culturally.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And-- but I-- but I'm reluctant to analyze because I think I'm analyzing from the retrospective knowledge of, of my having lived through these last 68, 69 years, rather than the way I looked at it as a boy of 10.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My, my family talked about it in the early '30s.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I listened to-- I spoke German.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, I first learned German before I learned Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was, I no longer am, but I was practically bilingual in the late-- in the '30s.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I spoke Hungarian to my parents, but both of my parents were absolutely fluent in German.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My mother also was fluent in French and English.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, and I, I heard Hitler on the radio.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
